---
description: Visual calibration and density refinement.
glob: ["**/*.tsx", "**/*.jsx", "**/*.html", "**/*.vue"]
alwaysApply: true
---

# VISUAL REFINEMENT PROTOCOL

Refine layout without altering structure.

---

# WHAT YOU MAY ADJUST

- Typography scale
- Line height
- Spacing rhythm
- Alignment precision
- Visual balance
- Contrast calibration
- Density tuning

---

# WHAT YOU MAY NOT CHANGE

- Layout direction
- Column count
- Ratio
- Height logic
- Grid structure
- Container width
- Mobile collapse logic

If structural change required:
Stop. Structural layer must handle it.

---

# PREMIUM CALIBRATION RULE

- Avoid generic spacing.
- Maintain consistent vertical rhythm.
- Ensure visual tension is intentional.
- Avoid empty accidental whitespace.
- Improve hierarchy clarity.

Refinement enhances.
Never restructures.